5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 267, L.D. 413, “An Act Regarding
10 Disclosure by Sellers of Residential Real Property of Notices of Shoreland Zoning
11 Ordinance Violations”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 33 MRSA §173, sub-§8, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 602, §5 and reallocated
15 by RR 2023, c. 2, Pt. A, §52, is repealed and the following enacted in its place:
16 8. Shoreland zoning ordinance. Detailed information on any of the following related
17 to a shoreland zoning ordinance adopted pursuant to Title 38, chapter 3, subchapter 1,
18 article 2-B:
19 A. A notice of violation issued by a municipal official or state agency;
20 B. A pending enforcement action;
21 C. Litigation;
22 D. A court judgment; and
23 E. A settlement or consent agreement.'
24 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
25 number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment specifies the information a seller
2288 of residential real property must disclose related to violations and enforcement and court
2299 actions with respect to a shoreland zoning ordinance.
